{"questionId":"27757","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>, let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> be the line passing through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> has the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi></math>.&nbsp;Show that the lines&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;are skew.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>point on line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> has coordinates&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use a different parameter for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>μ</mi></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>point on line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;has coordinates&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>μ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>μ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> This <em><strong>A1</strong></em> may be implied by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>μ</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>μ</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi></math></p>\n<p>any two of the above equations&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve two simultaneous equations with two parameters&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitute into third equation or solve a different pair of simultaneous equations&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>obtain contradiction <em>eg</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;or</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (so the lines do not intersect)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award this<em><strong> R1</strong></em> if it is based on incorrect values.</p>\n<p><br>lines are not parallel&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so lines are skew&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><br></p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>point on line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;has coordinates&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use the equation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> to generate at least two equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>if the two lines intersect,</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>⇒</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>any two of the above equations&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve at least one equation in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>one of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;seen&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitute into second equation or solve second equation&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>obtain contradiction eg&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;(so the lines do not intersect)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award this <strong>R1</strong> if it is based on incorrect values.</p>\n<p><br>lines are not parallel&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so lines are skew&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br><br></p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use a find Cartesian equation for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to isolate one variable in both equations&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>z</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve for each of the other two variables&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>obtain contradiction <em>eg</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math></p>\n<p>(so the lines do not intersect)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Do not award this&nbsp;<strong>R1</strong>&nbsp;if it is based on incorrect values.</p>\n<p><br>lines are not parallel&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so lines are skew&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[8 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27757","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.12c.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Line L2 has the equation x-12=y3=1-z. Show that the lines L1 and L2 are skew.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 8]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.15—Classification of lines"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}